HEADWORD: Boustrophedon
<hw>Bou`stro*phe"don</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/ turning like oxen in plowing; <?/ to turn.]</ety> <def>An ancient
mode of writing, in alternate directions, one line from left to right,
and the next from right to left (as fields are plowed), as in early
Greek and Hittite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

